Diagnosis.
Head 1.16 as wide as mesosoma (
Fig. 4D
), distinctly narrowed behind, dense and coarse punctured (
Fig. 4F
). Diameter of ocellus 0.6 × as long as distance between lateral ocellus and eye. Face 1.5 as wide as high (
Fig. 4E
). Clypeus convex basally, with rare punctures and blunt apical ridge. Upper tooth of mandible slightly longer than lower tooth. Flagellum with 43 filiform segments. First segment 3.5 × as long as wide, penultimate segment 2.5 × as long as wide. Epomia and notaulus weakly developed. Scutellum not carinated and partly rugoso-punctured. Fore wing with areolet pointed from above shortly petiolate. Nervulus distinctly postfurcal, pleural vein joined postnervulus almost below middle. Hind wing with 9 distal hamuli. Nervellus strongly reclival, intercepted in middle. Legs moderately slender. Hind femur 6.1 × as long as wide. First tergite slender, 1.8 × as long as wide, moderately dense and coarsely punctured, with longitudinal concavity in middle to apical margin. Entirely black. Frons with two small yellow spots on inner orbit. Antenna entirely black. Two spots on fronto-lateral part of mesonotum yellow. Legs black. Fore and mid tibia and tarsus dark brown.
